                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d162">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">835.6363/468: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Argentina</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Weddell</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-10-10T14:00:00-05:00"
                            >October 10, 1936—2 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>134. Your 213, October 8, 6 p.m. You are authorized in your discretion to inform
                    the Minister of Foreign Affairs of the hope of this Government that equality of
                    treatment will prevail in dealing with the oil companies, both as regards the
                    proposed marketing arrangement and under the by-law passed by the City Council
                    on October 6.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
